sql:
SELECT name, workload
FROM support_agents
WHERE status = 'active';

SELECT metric_value
FROM support_metrics
WHERE metric_name = 'resolution rate';

SELECT AVG(metric_value) AS average_resolution_rate
FROM support_metrics
WHERE metric_name = 'resolution rate';

SELECT COUNT(tag_id) AS tag_count
FROM ticket_tags
WHERE ticket_id = 1224;

SELECT COUNT(comment_id) AS comment_count
FROM ticket_comments
WHERE customer_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS resolved_tickets
FROM ticket_history
WHERE agent_id = 1 AND is_resolved = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Average response time is calculated in minutes; 
- A response time greater than 5 minutes is considered slow; 
- Active customers are those who have an ongoing interaction or subscription with the company.

- Active support agents are those who are currently available to handle new tickets;
- A ticket is considered resolved when the 'is_resolved' flag is set to 1 in the ticket history;
- The 'workload' refers to the current number of tickets assigned to a support agent;
- The 'last month' refers to the 30-day period preceding the current date.

